5000|$|Multiple-prism <b>beam</b> <b>expanders</b> usually deploy {{two to five}} prism {{to yield}} large {{one-dimensional}} beam expansion factors. Designs applicable to tunable lasers with beam expansion factors of up to 200 have been disclosed in the literature. Initially multiple-prism grating configurations were introduced in narrow-linewidth liquid dye lasers but eventually were also adopted in gas, solid-state, and diode laser designs. [...] The generalized mathematical description of multiple-prism <b>beam</b> <b>expanders,</b> introduced by Duarte, [...] {{is known as the}} multiple-prism dispersion theory.|$|R
